  "milestone3Body": "Your dopamine pathways are starting to reset. Your body is becoming more 'insulin-sensitive,' which is fantastic for your long-term health.",
  "milestone3Mind": "You've made it through the hardest part of the initial withdrawal. From here, the physical cravings will start to subside.",
  "milestone5Title": "Day 5: Gut Guardian",
  "milestone5Body": "The 'bad' bacteria in your gut that thrive on sugar are starting to die off. This makes room for beneficial bacteria to flourish, improving digestion and overall gut health.",
  "milestone5Mind": "You're noticing a pattern and proving to yourself that you don't need sugar to get through the day.",
  "milestone7Title": "Day 7: The Taste Bud Reset",
  "milestone7Body": "Your taste buds are no longer desensitized by overwhelming sweetness. An apple or a strawberry will start to taste incredibly sweet and flavorful.",
  "milestone7Mind": "A major milestone! You've completed a full week. The habit is beginning to form.",
  "milestone14Title": "Day 14: The Glow Up",
  "milestone14Body": "Sugar damages collagen. By cutting it out, you're stopping this damage. Reduced inflammation can lead to clearer, calmer skin.",
  "milestone14Mind": "Two weeks! Your commitment is solidifying. This is no longer a fluke; it's a lifestyle change.",
  "milestone21Title": "Day 21: The Habit Loop",
  "milestone21Body": "Your brain has had enough time to start forming new neural pathways. Reaching for a healthy snack instead of a sugary one feels more natural.",
  "milestone21Mind": "They say it takes 21 days to form a habit. You've just laid the foundation for a permanent, positive change.",
  "milestone30Title": "Day 30: The Energy Upgrade",
  "milestone30Body": "Your body is now efficient at using fat for fuel, leading to more stable energy without the afternoon crashes. Your triglyceride levels have likely dropped significantly.",
  "milestone30Mind": "You've conquered a whole month. Your self-efficacy is sky-high. You are in control.",
  "milestone40Title": "Day 40: The Dental Dividend",
  "milestone40Body": "The harmful bacteria in your mouth that cause cavities thrive on sugar. By starving them, you're dramatically improving your oral health and reducing inflammation in your gums.",
  "milestone40Mind": "Your mouth feels cleaner, and you're investing in a future with fewer dental bills. That's a reason to smile.",
  "milestone60Title": "Day 60: Deeper Sleep",
  "milestone60Body": "Without blood sugar spikes and crashes disrupting your night, your body can achieve deeper, more restorative sleep cycles. This improves everything from memory to mood.",
  "milestone60Mind": "Waking up feeling genuinely rested becomes the new normal, not the exception.",
  "milestone75Title": "Day 75: Autophagy Activated",
  "milestone75Body": "With lower insulin levels, your body's cellular cleanup process, known as 'autophagy,' can work more effectively. It's like a deep spring-cleaning for your cells, removing damaged parts.",
  "milestone75Mind": "You're not just looking better, you are fundamentally healthier on a cellular level. This is deep healing.",
  "milestone90Title": "Day 90: Mental Sharpness",
  "milestone90Body": "Reduced inflammation in the brain and stable energy supply leads to less 'brain fog,' better focus, and improved memory recall.",
  "milestone90Mind": "You feel sharper and more clear-headed. Complex tasks seem less daunting.",
  "milestone120Title": "4 Months: The Immune Boost",
  "milestone120Body": "High sugar intake can impair the function of your white blood cells. After four months, your immune system is operating without this handicap, better equipped to fight off infections.",
  "milestone120Mind": "You're building a more resilient body, one that's better prepared to defend itself.",
